article.description: NASSAU, Bahamas --  Alex Montgomery scored 16 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Georgia Tech (unranked ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) to its fifth straight win, a 65-27 victory over Winthrop on Thursday night.
article.headline: Montgomery's double-double helps Georgia Tech to win
article.linkText: Montgomery helps Ga. Tech to fifth straight win
article.story:
NASSAU, Bahamas --  Alex Montgomery scored 16 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Georgia Tech (unranked ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) to its fifth straight win, a 65-27 victory over Winthrop on Thursday night.

The Yellow Jackets (9-2) limited the Eagles to four points in the first 8:34 of the game at the Bahamas SunSplash Shootout.

Georgia Tech led 37-14 at halftime, then held Winthrop (4-4) scoreless in the first seven minutes of the second half.

The Yellow Jackets made 24 of 44 shots in the game (54.5 percent) while the Eagles made only 11 of 45 field goals (24.4 percent). Georgia Tech also outrebounded Winthrop 37-15.

The Yellow Jackets broke into the Top 25 poll this week for the second time in 15 years and the first time since Jan. 21, 2008, when they ranked No. 23.

Jacqua Williams added 13 points for Georgia Tech.

Ashley Haugtvedt led Winthrop with 10 points.
